name: Poiesis #01
description:
“It's the road that matters, not the destination” is a phrase that comes from the poem Ithaca by Constantine Cavafy (1863 - 1933). The poem Ithaca reminds us that themost important part of a journey is to travel the road, any road, and not just to long for the destination. 
Some of Cavafy's poems have become proverbial and can be extended to many processes in our lives.
